    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-08T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-08T04:00:00-05:00" n="107"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 U.S.S.R./66: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_BWC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-08T12:00:00+03:00"
                            >June 8, 1934—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 8—8:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>124. Your 108, June 6, 4 p.m. I shall see <persName corresp="#p_KNN1"
                        >Krestinsky</persName> tomorrow and then reply fully. Until I can report
                        <persName corresp="#p_KNN1">Krestinsky</persName>’s views I believe that it
                    would be inadvisable for the Department to negotiate with <persName
                        corresp="#p_TAA1">Troyanovsky</persName> who may or may not represent the
                    point of view of his Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
